\section*{Section A: \ \ \ Pure Mathematics}

%%%%%%%%%%Q1

Given that $a$ is constant, differentiate the following expressions
with respect to $x$: 

\begin{itemize}
\setlength{\itemsep}{3mm}
\item[\bf (i)]  $x^{a}$; 
\item[\bf (ii)] $a^{x}$; 
\item[\bf (iii)] $x^{x}$; 
\item[\bf (iv)] $x^{(x^{x})}$;
